WEBVTT

00:00:22.417 --> 00:00:23.917
"ALfheim, Neutral Territory"

00:00:23.917 --> 00:00:26.125
"Central Capital, Arun"

00:00:39.083 --> 00:00:40.708
The World Tree...

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.792
Yeah, no question about it.
This is Arun!

00:00:44.792 --> 00:00:48.667
The center of ALfheim,
the biggest city in the world.

00:00:48.667 --> 00:00:51.250
We're finally here.

00:00:51.583 --> 00:00:55.500
I've never been to a city this size.

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:57.083
Me neither.

00:00:57.083 --> 00:01:00.917
The ore light looks like stardust...

00:01:04.333 --> 00:01:12.583
<i>The server will be down today, January 22nd,</i>
<i>from 4:00 AM to 3:00 PM for scheduled maintenance.</i>

00:01:13.167 --> 00:01:17.500
<i>Players are asked to log out</i>
<i>10 minutes in advance.</i>

00:01:18.167 --> 00:01:22.167
<i>Repeat: The server will be down today,</i>
<i>January 22nd, from 4:00 AM to 3:00 PM...</i>

00:01:22.167 --> 00:01:26.333
That's all for today, huh?
Let's log out at an inn.

00:01:27.333 --> 00:01:28.542
Yeah...

00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:32.917
Well, let's find an inn.

00:01:32.917 --> 00:01:36.833
I blew all my cash,
so nowhere too pricey.

00:01:36.833 --> 00:01:41.458
That's because you were showing off
by giving all your money to Sakuya.

00:01:41.458 --> 00:01:44.125
You should have
saved money for an inn.

00:01:46.125 --> 00:01:50.042
You heard your dad.
Is there a cheap inn nearby?

00:01:50.958 --> 00:01:52.417
Hmm...

00:01:52.417 --> 00:01:55.792
There's a super-cheap one down there.

00:01:55.958 --> 00:01:58.458
S-Super-cheap, huh?

00:01:58.458 --> 00:01:59.708
Let's go.

00:01:59.708 --> 00:02:01.833
Ah, wait, Kirito...

00:02:12.625 --> 00:02:18.083
<i>The feelings I've hidden</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:02:18.083 --> 00:02:23.583
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:02:33.708 --> 00:02:44.083
<i>Seeking only a miracle, I wander</i>
<i>through an endless darkness</i>

00:02:44.292 --> 00:02:54.833
<i>If I stay here, I won't</i>
<i>ever see the future again</i>

00:02:54.917 --> 00:03:00.167
<i>Tonight the moon summons me again.</i>
<i>Though I still cannot speak,</i>

00:03:00.167 --> 00:03:03.958
<i>I keep crying out in my heart</i>

00:03:05.083 --> 00:03:10.292
<i>My hidden feelings</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:03:10.417 --> 00:03:15.333
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:03:15.500 --> 00:03:21.208
<i>If I can stay stronger a bit longer,</i>

00:03:21.208 --> 00:03:27.292
<i>I will go beyond</i>
<i>this sky right in front of me</i>

00:03:29.083 --> 00:03:35.583
<i>I will reach out towards</i>
<i>the future ahead of me</i>

00:03:41.042 --> 00:03:45.042
"The Truth About ALfheim"

00:03:56.417 --> 00:03:57.792
<i>Is that a...</i>

00:04:35.667 --> 00:04:37.000
Morning, Sugu.

00:04:37.292 --> 00:04:39.583
Morning, Big Brother.

00:04:42.375 --> 00:04:46.875
You look really sleepy.
When did you get to bed last night?

00:04:46.875 --> 00:04:49.875
Let's see... Four, I think?

00:04:50.083 --> 00:04:55.000
A kid shouldn't stay up that late.
What were you doing?

00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:58.292
I guess I was on the Internet...

00:05:00.542 --> 00:05:02.667
You'd better go easy on that.

00:05:03.625 --> 00:05:05.875
Not that I should talk.

00:05:07.250 --> 00:05:08.542
Hey, Sugu.

00:05:08.542 --> 00:05:09.875
Turn around.

00:05:10.375 --> 00:05:11.833
Just do it.

00:05:13.583 --> 00:05:14.833
Like this?

00:05:31.833 --> 00:05:33.958
<i>How far does this go?</i>

00:05:47.167 --> 00:05:49.458
<i>Is this a map?</i>

00:05:51.917 --> 00:05:53.167
<i>Somewhere...</i>

00:05:54.292 --> 00:05:57.333
<i>Somewhere there's a console</i>
<i>where I can log out.</i>

00:06:02.667 --> 00:06:04.208
<i>Experiment Hangar?</i>

00:06:18.250 --> 00:06:23.583
Big Brother, you'd better buy me a green tea
raspberry cream parfait to make up for before.

00:06:23.583 --> 00:06:25.167
For sure, okay?

00:06:25.333 --> 00:06:26.708
Sure.

00:06:26.875 --> 00:06:30.750
Then you're forgiven.
So do you want to get it today?

00:06:32.333 --> 00:06:35.500
I have to do something
in the afternoon.

00:06:35.750 --> 00:06:39.083
And I'm planning to go
to the hospital this morning.

00:06:39.917 --> 00:06:41.042
Oh...

00:06:43.542 --> 00:06:45.375
Hey, Big Brother...

00:06:45.375 --> 00:06:48.292
Could I come with you?

00:06:50.667 --> 00:06:52.500
Oh, sure.

00:06:53.125 --> 00:06:55.417
I'm sure that will make Asuna happy.

00:06:55.750 --> 00:06:56.750
Yeah.

00:06:58.292 --> 00:07:00.417
All right, let's eat!

00:07:29.417 --> 00:07:30.792
This is...

00:07:30.792 --> 00:07:33.375
By expanding the brain's control regions,

00:07:33.375 --> 00:07:38.583
it's possible it could control
thought, emotion, even memory.

00:07:43.125 --> 00:07:44.625
They're suffering!

00:07:47.083 --> 00:07:49.625
Are... all of these?

00:07:53.833 --> 00:07:54.833
How...

00:07:55.667 --> 00:07:57.208
How awful!

00:08:03.917 --> 00:08:05.875
He won't get away with this.

00:08:06.208 --> 00:08:08.458
No, I won't let him!

00:08:09.250 --> 00:08:12.583
Just wait a little. I'll save you
as soon as I can, okay?

00:08:16.042 --> 00:08:18.375
Now, how's it going?

00:08:19.333 --> 00:08:22.458
He's having another dream about Spica.

00:08:22.458 --> 00:08:27.833
The B-13 and B-14 fields are
off the scale. Same with 16.

00:08:27.833 --> 00:08:29.583
High excitement.

00:08:29.583 --> 00:08:33.042
Sure it isn't a coincidence?
It's only been three times.

00:08:33.042 --> 00:08:36.708
No, it's due to the emotional
inducement circuits.

00:08:36.708 --> 00:08:40.375
If it's happening at this rate,
he's over the threshold.

00:08:41.583 --> 00:08:44.875
For now, put him down for
continuous monitoring.

00:08:44.875 --> 00:08:48.750
"Next Bus Arriving Soon
Shin Tokorozawa Station East Exit"
Hey, Big Brother, what about school?

00:08:48.750 --> 00:08:49.833
School?

00:08:49.833 --> 00:08:54.375
Weren't you supposed to start
high school last year?

00:08:54.708 --> 00:08:56.167
Well...

00:08:56.167 --> 00:09:00.708
They said something about using
one of the empty public school buildings

00:09:00.708 --> 00:09:06.750
as a temporary school for
the students who came back from SAO.

00:09:07.250 --> 00:09:08.667
<i>Now departing.</i>

00:09:08.958 --> 00:09:10.917
There's no entrance exam,

00:09:10.917 --> 00:09:14.625
and after graduating, you'll be
qualified to take the college exams.

00:09:15.167 --> 00:09:16.333
I see.

00:09:16.792 --> 00:09:19.833
That sounds like a good deal...

00:09:20.292 --> 00:09:23.042
But they'll be lumping lots of
different students together.

00:09:24.417 --> 00:09:30.417
After all, we spent over two years playing
a brutal death game on a daily basis.

00:09:30.417 --> 00:09:35.875
They don't know what it did to our minds.
Maybe we'll be together for observation.

00:09:35.875 --> 00:09:37.375
Seriously?

00:09:37.875 --> 00:09:41.667
But if I wanted to get into
a high school the normal way,

00:09:41.667 --> 00:09:46.083
I'd have to start from scratch and
spend the whole year at cram school.

00:09:46.250 --> 00:09:50.708
Of course, if I wanted to take the exam
on my own, I'm sure I could.

00:09:50.958 --> 00:09:53.458
I'm sure you'd do fine.

00:09:53.458 --> 00:09:55.542
Your grades are good.

00:09:55.542 --> 00:09:59.417
"Were." Past tense.
I haven't studied for two years.

00:09:59.875 --> 00:10:02.667
Then I'll tutor you!

00:10:03.500 --> 00:10:06.792
Then maybe you'll help me with
math and information processing.

00:10:20.333 --> 00:10:21.583
<i>That's...</i>

00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:27.000
<i>A system console?</i>

00:10:29.583 --> 00:10:31.833
<i>Good, they haven't seen me yet.</i>

00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:42.750
<i>Please!</i>

00:10:53.000 --> 00:10:53.542
"Leave Virtual Laboratory"

00:10:53.542 --> 00:10:54.375
"Leave Virtual Laboratory"
<i>This is it!</i>

00:10:54.375 --> 00:10:55.708
"Terminate all services and log out."
"Cancel"       "Log Out"

00:10:57.125 --> 00:10:59.083
"Terminate all services and log out."
"Cancel"       "Log Out"

00:11:04.833 --> 00:11:06.917
What a big hospital.

00:11:06.917 --> 00:11:09.917
It's amazing inside too. Like a hotel.

00:11:28.208 --> 00:11:30.458
"Asuna Yuki."

00:11:31.083 --> 00:11:33.917
Her character shared her real name.

00:11:33.917 --> 00:11:36.375
Not many people do that.

00:11:36.750 --> 00:11:38.833
You know a lot about it...

00:11:39.583 --> 00:11:43.458
Asuna's the only one I've ever known
to play under her real name.

00:11:48.125 --> 00:11:51.167
I'll introduce you. This is Asuna.

00:11:51.333 --> 00:11:55.417
Vice commander of the Knights
of the Blood Oath, Lightning Flash Asuna.

00:11:55.583 --> 00:11:59.875
I never was able to match her
sword speed or accuracy.

00:12:00.333 --> 00:12:03.250
Asuna, this is my sister, Suguha.

00:12:04.583 --> 00:12:07.792
N-Nice to meet you, Asuna.

00:12:12.500 --> 00:12:14.625
"Log Out"

00:12:18.167 --> 00:12:21.375
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

00:12:24.542 --> 00:12:26.667
Hey, put me down.

00:12:26.833 --> 00:12:29.083
I'm a friend of Sugou.

00:12:29.250 --> 00:12:33.208
He was letting me look around.
I'm leaving now.

00:12:33.208 --> 00:12:36.375
No one notified me about this.

00:12:36.708 --> 00:12:38.250
What about you?

00:12:38.250 --> 00:12:39.500
Nothing.

00:12:39.667 --> 00:12:43.208
He wouldn't want outsiders
seeing this anyway.

00:12:45.042 --> 00:12:46.333
Hold on.

00:12:46.500 --> 00:12:51.042
You're that girl Sugou keeps
at the top of the World Tree.

00:12:51.042 --> 00:12:54.958
I've heard about that.

00:12:54.958 --> 00:13:00.125
It's so unfair that the boss gets to
have all the fun with the cute girl.

00:13:01.333 --> 00:13:03.917
Come on, keep still.

00:13:03.917 --> 00:13:06.458
Stop it!
Let me go, monster!

00:13:06.583 --> 00:13:08.750
That's so mean...

00:13:08.750 --> 00:13:12.500
We're in the midst of an experiment
on deep-sense mapping.

00:13:12.667 --> 00:13:14.917
You're scientists, aren't you?

00:13:14.917 --> 00:13:21.083
You aren't ashamed, participating in
this illegal, unethical experiment?

00:13:22.167 --> 00:13:27.917
I think it's more ethical than sticking
electrical probes into an exposed animal brain.

00:13:27.917 --> 00:13:31.542
They're all just dreaming.

00:13:31.667 --> 00:13:33.042
That's right.

00:13:33.042 --> 00:13:37.083
Sometimes, we show them
the most wonderful dreams.

00:13:37.083 --> 00:13:39.542
I wish I were in their shoes.

00:13:41.083 --> 00:13:42.375
You're insane.

00:13:43.208 --> 00:13:48.250
The boss is on a trip, right? Get back to
the other side, and see what he wants to do.

00:13:48.875 --> 00:13:53.917
Fine... Hey, don't have any fun
without me while I'm gone.

00:13:53.917 --> 00:13:56.458
Got it, got it.
Get going.

00:14:02.208 --> 00:14:05.250
Release me!
Let me go! Let me out!

00:14:05.250 --> 00:14:06.750
I can't!

00:14:06.750 --> 00:14:08.917
The boss would kill me!

00:14:08.917 --> 00:14:10.417
But anyway...

00:14:10.417 --> 00:14:16.667
Why don't we enjoy some
electro-drugs? I'm sick of dolls.

00:14:19.250 --> 00:14:21.500
S-Stop it!

00:14:22.667 --> 00:14:24.125
What are you doing?

00:14:26.083 --> 00:14:27.125
Stop...

00:14:36.458 --> 00:14:39.250
Stop! Fine! Fine...

00:14:41.208 --> 00:14:44.667
I forgot I turned off
the pain absorber.

00:14:45.667 --> 00:14:47.542
What are you doing?

00:14:47.708 --> 00:14:51.583
Nothing. Anyway, what did the boss say?

00:14:51.583 --> 00:14:53.375
He was livid.

00:14:53.583 --> 00:14:59.958
He said to return her to the birdcage above the lab,
change the code, and monitor her 24/7.

00:14:59.958 --> 00:15:02.958
And I was just about
to have some fun...

00:15:03.042 --> 00:15:09.375
Let's at least walk her back instead of
teleporting. I want to feel her a little more.

00:15:09.375 --> 00:15:12.083
This really turns you on, doesn't it?

00:15:14.250 --> 00:15:17.417
Come on, no more struggling.

00:15:19.083 --> 00:15:20.958
--Stay put.
--I said release me!

00:15:22.333 --> 00:15:24.167
<i>She's so pretty.</i>

00:15:24.792 --> 00:15:28.000
<i>It's a shame that she's still asleep.</i>

00:15:31.333 --> 00:15:34.583
<i>Maybe I shouldn't have come.</i>

00:15:35.875 --> 00:15:39.500
<i>I don't know how I feel.</i>

00:15:41.083 --> 00:15:44.167
<i>I thought if I met Asuna, I'd know.</i>

00:15:44.708 --> 00:15:45.833
<i>But...</i>

00:15:46.167 --> 00:15:50.375
<i>...do I want to be a good sister?</i>

00:15:52.792 --> 00:15:54.375
<i>Or do I...</i>

00:16:12.833 --> 00:16:14.333
<i>Big Brother.</i>

00:16:20.292 --> 00:16:24.417
Bye. Let's play again
if we have the chance.

00:16:31.042 --> 00:16:34.167
<i>I won't lose, Kirito.</i>

00:16:34.917 --> 00:16:39.792
<i>I will never give up.</i>
<i>I will escape this place!</i>

00:16:55.875 --> 00:16:57.042
Leafa?

00:17:01.042 --> 00:17:02.917
What's wrong, Leafa?

00:17:04.333 --> 00:17:05.542
Um...

00:17:06.458 --> 00:17:08.458
Um, Kirito...

00:17:08.917 --> 00:17:11.583
I... I...

00:17:12.125 --> 00:17:14.208
My heart was just broken...

00:17:18.958 --> 00:17:23.667
I'm sorry, saying all this
to someone I just met.

00:17:23.875 --> 00:17:28.708
It's against etiquette to bring
real-world problems here.

00:17:29.625 --> 00:17:33.792
Whether you're here or in the real world,
you can cry when it hurts.

00:17:34.250 --> 00:17:38.750
There's no rule that you can't
show feelings just because it's a game.

00:17:39.958 --> 00:17:41.167
Kirito...

00:17:45.583 --> 00:17:47.917
<i>I'm in love with my brother.</i>

00:17:48.958 --> 00:17:52.708
<i>I can't ever speak of these feelings.</i>

00:17:54.125 --> 00:17:57.542
<i>I have to bury them deep in my heart.</i>

00:17:58.583 --> 00:18:01.625
<i>So that I can forget them someday.</i>

00:18:11.875 --> 00:18:15.833
I'm okay. Thanks, Kirito.

00:18:17.458 --> 00:18:19.417
You're sweet, aren't you?

00:18:19.708 --> 00:18:23.375
People often say the exact
opposite about me.

00:18:23.792 --> 00:18:28.500
Want to log off for today? I think I can
make it the rest of the way myself.

00:18:28.708 --> 00:18:29.875
No...

00:18:29.875 --> 00:18:33.292
I've come this far.
I'll go the rest of the way.

00:18:36.833 --> 00:18:38.458
Now, let's go.

00:18:46.125 --> 00:18:47.958
Yui, you here?

00:18:51.375 --> 00:18:54.500
Good morning, Daddy and Leafa.

00:18:54.792 --> 00:18:56.375
Morning, Yui.

00:18:56.625 --> 00:19:02.458
Hey, I was wondering yesterday...
Um... Do Navi-Pixies sleep at night?

00:19:02.458 --> 00:19:05.708
Of course not.
But when Daddy's not here,

00:19:05.708 --> 00:19:09.917
I shut down my input circuits
and process accumulated data.

00:19:09.917 --> 00:19:13.292
It could be similar to human sleep.

00:19:13.292 --> 00:19:15.292
But you just yawned...

00:19:15.292 --> 00:19:22.292
That's what humans do during their boot-up sequence,
right? On average, Daddy's last eight seconds.

00:19:22.292 --> 00:19:24.958
You don't have to tell us
odd things like that.

00:19:26.375 --> 00:19:27.958
Okay, let's go.

00:19:27.958 --> 00:19:28.958
Yeah.

00:19:32.250 --> 00:19:34.458
It's really bustling.

00:19:34.458 --> 00:19:37.417
I guess it really is
the center of ALfheim.

00:19:37.667 --> 00:19:42.500
It seems that all the fairy races
from around the continent are here.

00:20:03.250 --> 00:20:06.042
That's the World Tree.

00:20:09.417 --> 00:20:10.708
Yeah.

00:20:10.708 --> 00:20:13.667
Seeing it up close,
it's amazing, isn't it?

00:20:14.083 --> 00:20:18.250
Isn't there a city up there?

00:20:18.250 --> 00:20:19.375
And also...

00:20:19.833 --> 00:20:24.250
The Fairy King Oberon lives there
with the light fairies, the Alfs.

00:20:24.250 --> 00:20:29.458
And they say the first race to meet with
the king will be able to reincarnate as Alfs.

00:20:29.875 --> 00:20:32.750
You can't climb it on the outside?

00:20:32.917 --> 00:20:37.875
The area around the trunk is
off-limits, so you can't climb it.

00:20:38.417 --> 00:20:43.875
And your wings' flight limit would expire
long before you'd make it to the top.

00:20:44.167 --> 00:20:49.708
I heard that some people passed the limit
by launching off each other's shoulders...

00:20:49.708 --> 00:20:55.333
Oh, that story, huh? I hear they
made it pretty close to the branches.

00:20:55.333 --> 00:20:59.583
But the GMs freaked out
and patched it right away.

00:20:59.583 --> 00:21:03.792
Now there's a wall
just above the clouds.

00:21:03.792 --> 00:21:08.292
I see... For now, let's head
to the bottom of the tree.

00:21:08.292 --> 00:21:09.792
Yeah, got it.

00:21:29.583 --> 00:21:34.542
Once you pass through that gate, you're at
the world's heart, the central district of Arun.

00:21:44.292 --> 00:21:46.542
Hey, Yui. What's wrong?

00:21:47.500 --> 00:21:48.542
Mommy...

00:21:50.875 --> 00:21:53.208
Mommy is... here.

00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:56.125
You're sure?

00:21:56.125 --> 00:21:57.708
I'm certain.

00:21:57.708 --> 00:22:00.792
This player ID belongs to Mommy.

00:22:00.792 --> 00:22:04.208
The coordinates are right above us!

00:22:08.375 --> 00:22:09.542
Kirito!

00:22:10.792 --> 00:22:12.042
Wait!

00:22:12.375 --> 00:22:13.792
Kirito!

00:22:14.292 --> 00:22:16.125
Kirito!

00:22:17.917 --> 00:22:25.000
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:22:25.000 --> 00:22:34.708
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:22:46.083 --> 00:22:52.875
<i>These endless feelings were</i>
<i>swallowed up into my daily life</i>

00:22:53.250 --> 00:23:00.083
<i>Swaying as they</i>
<i>change shape yet again</i>

00:23:00.417 --> 00:23:07.333
<i>Is it too late now? I ask</i>
<i>myself but receive no answer</i>

00:23:07.458 --> 00:23:15.000
<i>It's all up to me now,</i>
<i>both the ending and the beginning</i>

00:23:15.167 --> 00:23:22.083
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:23:22.083 --> 00:23:29.292
<i>I'm going to spread my wings</i>
<i>and head towards that gentle light</i>

00:23:29.292 --> 00:23:36.708
<i>Carrying the passion</i>
<i>I've lit in my heart</i>

00:23:36.708 --> 00:23:44.917
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:23:47.042 --> 00:23:53.152
Next Time: "The Grand Quest."
